**Encountering foundation models in the wild**  
I recommend using Huggingface for the majority of these exercises. Please create an account and log in first. *Only* ChatGPT and Gemini are banned\! If you run out of credits, try shortly to find alternatives or just note how you would solve the task. 

*Question 1*  
What is he talking about? (Appendix A). 

*Question 2*  
Change the season, give her some weapon of your choice, and add a husband in the background (Appendix B). Otherwise figure out other ways to bring her to life\! I’ve heard Nano Banana, Flux Kontext, or Qwen Image Edit might be great. 

*Question 3*  
Create a 3D mesh of her. It’s alright to use the disappointed version. 

*Question 4*  
Damn, I accidentally ruined the quality of my picture. Upscale it (Appendix C).

*Question 5*  
Yesterday, the organizers of a conference told me they had around 600 participants. I’m skeptical. Use a tool to help provide a rough headcount (Appendix D).

*Question 6*  
Generate a fake news video (something which could be breaking or at least funny if true) by using any image from a news site as starting grounds. 

*Question 7*  
Make a nice music track — lyrics should be AI-generated, too — where your field of study is included in some way. Optional: a fitting album cover.

*Question 8*  
Rate at least 6 image generations and 3 text generations in arena-style ELO leaderboards. 

*Question 9*  
Interpolate between two frames of any video (or just any end points which might make sense), generating frames in-between.  
*Question 10*  
Grab an amount of headlines, e.g., 50\. Figure out how best to cluster them into topics and visualize representations of them.
